<topic xmlns:deltaxml="http://www.deltaxml.com/ns/well-formed-delta-v1" xmlns:dxx="http://www.deltaxml.com/ns/xml-namespaced-attribute" xmlns:dxa="http://www.deltaxml.com/ns/non-namespaced-attribute" xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" deltaxml:version-order="jupiter, sinope, carme, leda, kale" deltaxml:content-type="merge-concurrent" deltaxml:version="2.0" id="topic_xxs_klq_fh" deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope!=carme!=leda!=kale"><deltaxml:updates><deltaxml:update index="1" change="add"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="2" change="elementAdd"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="3" change="replace"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="4" change="elementDelete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="5" change="add"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="6" change="replace"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="7" change="delete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="8" change="elementDelete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="9" change="add"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="10" change="delete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="11" change="delete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="12" change="delete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="13" change="elementDelete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="14" change="modify"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="15" change="replace"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="16" change="modify"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="17" change="replace"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="18" change="modify"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="19" change="replace"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="20" change="delete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="21" change="delete"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="22" change="replace"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="23" change="replace"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="24" change="elementAdd"></deltaxml:update></deltaxml:updates><deltaxml:attribute-updates><deltaxml:update index="1" change="elementAdd"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="2" change="modify"></deltaxml:update><deltaxml:update index="3" change="elementAdd"></deltaxml:update></deltaxml:attribute-updates><title deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale!=carme"><deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="carme"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">An </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>Example for DeltaXML DITA Merge</title><body deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope!=carme!=leda!=kale"><section deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope!=carme!=leda"><title deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope=leda!=carme"><deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope=leda!=carme"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope=leda">Introduction</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">Preliminaries</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup></title><p deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope!=leda">Anna <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="leda"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="leda">and Chris </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>likes to do things properly and have introductions.</p></section><p deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope!=carme!=leda!=kale"><deltaxml:attributes deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope!=carme!=leda=kale"><dxa:id deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope"><deltaxml:attributeValue deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope">quick</deltaxml:attributeValue></dxa:id><dxx:lang deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope!=carme"><deltaxml:attributeValue deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter">en</deltaxml:attributeValue><deltaxml:attributeValue deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope">en-GB</deltaxml:attributeValue><deltaxml:attributeValue deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">en-US</deltaxml:attributeValue></dxx:lang></deltaxml:attributes>DeltaXML DITA Merge automatically merges edits from two or more <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale!=carme"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale">editors</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">reviewers</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup> into a single document, so you can accept/reject changes from multiple authors all in one document. With <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale">DeltaXML </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>DITA Merge you are no longer restricted to having only one person working on a document.</p><p deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale!=sinope">It is relatively easy to work on a document which is reviewed by one other person because you just need to compare two documents (or record changes) to see the changes. If there are two reviewers, then it <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope">suddenly </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>becomes a lot more complicated, because you need to do two comparisons and then view three different documents (changes from each reviewer and your original) to produce a new version. For three or more reviewers, you soon run out of screen space to see what is going on.</p><p deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale!=sinope=leda">Now, with <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale">DeltaXML </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>DITA Merge, this job becomes much, much easier, because <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale">DeltaXML </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>DITA Merge merges all the changes into a single document.</p><p deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale!=sinope=leda"><deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale">DeltaXML </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>DITA Merge has a number of different use cases:</p><ul deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope!=carme!=leda!=kale"><deltaxml:attributes deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=carme=leda!=kale"><dxa:id deltaxml:deltaV2="kale"><deltaxml:attributeValue deltaxml:deltaV2="kale">ul_j3n_cmq_fh</deltaxml:attributeValue></dxa:id></deltaxml:attributes><li deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=carme=leda=kale"><p>accept or reject changes from multiple reviewers by working on just one document</p></li><li deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=leda=kale"><p>allow more than one editor to work on a document simultaneously and merge their changes together</p></li><li deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope!=carme!=leda!=kale"><p deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope!=carme!=leda!=kale">allow intelligent resolution of conflicts in a <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter!=sinope=carme=leda!=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter">Content Managment</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope=carme=leda">Content Management</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="kale">Document Management</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup> System (<deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=carme=leda!=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=carme=leda">CMS</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="kale">DMS</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>) when <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=leda=kale!=sinope!=carme"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=leda=kale">two users check </deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope">multiple users check </deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">more than one user checks </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>in the same <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale!=carme"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale">edited</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">reviewed</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup> document</p></li><li deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=leda!=sinope!=carme!=kale"><p deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=leda!=sinope!=carme!=kale">merge changes from <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=leda=kale!=sinope!=carme"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=leda=kale">two</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="sinope">multiple</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">many</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup> different branches in a <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=carme=leda!=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=carme=leda">CMS</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="kale">DMS</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup></p></li></ul><p deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=kale!=sinope=leda!=carme"><deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale">DeltaXML </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>DITA Merge works at the level of each paragraph, table or list. <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=carme=kale">DeltaXML </deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup>DITA Merge compares each <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale!=carme"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale">edited</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">reviewed</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup> version with the base and if only one is different, the changes are shown as tracked changes so that they can be accepted or rejected.</p><p deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale!=carme">If more than one editor has changed the same item, the change from each <deltaxml:textGroup deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale!=carme"><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="jupiter=sinope=leda=kale">editor</deltaxml:text><deltaxml:text deltaxml:deltaV2="carme">reviewer</deltaxml:text></deltaxml:textGroup> is shown separately for easier understanding. At the same time, all the changes are intelligently merged into one copy of the paragraph or item to make it easier to accept or reject each change.</p><p deltaxml:deltaV2="kale">DeltaXML DITA Merge is available as a Java API for integration into your existing DMS or other enterprise systems. Please contact us for further details.</p></body></topic>